{
  "texts": [
    "a covering space) on ∂ whose sections on open intervals in ∂ are holomorphic functions of the form i a i z k i on the corresponding germs of open sectors, where k i ∈ Q >0, and a i ∈ C. Each connected component of (the étalé space of) such a local section is a finite order cover of the circle ∂.",
    "More precisely, let r be the smallest integer such that the expression q = i a i z k i is a polynomial in z 1/r.",
    "The corresponding holomorphic function is multivalued, and becomes single-valued when passing to a finite covering t r = z.",
    "Therefore, the corresponding connected component of I, which we denote by ⟨q⟩, is an r-sheeted covering of ∂.",
    "As a topological space, it is homeomorphic to a circle, and I is thus a disjoint union of (an infinite number of) circles."
  ]
}